  "general_provisions": "This bill creates the School Safety Support Program to provide funding for school safety requirements and infrastructure.",
  "hilighted_provisions": "This bill:<hr><ltbullet>creates the School Safety Support Program (program) to fund school safety personnel, building standards, emergency protocols, and security infrastructure;<hr><ltbullet>establishes a distribution formula that allocates funding to charter schools and school districts based on enrollment and base amounts;<hr><ltbullet>requires local education agencies to submit safety plans and annual reports to receive funding;<hr><ltbullet>adds the program to the list of education programs eligible for annual inflation and enrollment growth adjustments;<hr><ltbullet>protects the program from funding reductions due to negative enrollment growth;<hr><ltbullet>directs the state board to collaborate with the School Safety Center and state security chief to establish rules and monitor implementation; and<hr><ltbullet>makes technical changes.",
